post_cb({"29449097": {"Id": "29449097", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>The size of an array shall be a constant expression (greater than 0). Change this declaration</p>\n<pre><code>int BARIS = 8;\n</code></pre>\n<p>to</p>\n<pre><code>const int BARIS = 8;\n</code></pre>\n<p>The C++ Standard does not allow Variable Length Arrays (VLA) though some compilers have their own language extensions that allow to use VLA(s).  And moreover VLA(s) shall have automatic storage duration. That is if you are allowed to define a VLA then it shall be a local array</p>\n<p>From the C Standard where VLA(s) are allowed (6.7.6.2 Array declarators)</p>\n<blockquote id=\"so_29448997_29449097_0\">\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>...If an identifier is declared to be an object with static or thread storage duration, <strong>it shall not have a variable length array\n  type</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If the variable may not be constant then use <code>std::vector&lt;int&gt;</code> instead of the array. For example</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;vector&gt;\n\n//...\n\nint BARIS = 8;\nstd::vector&lt;int&gt; SquaresInfo( BARIS );\n</code></pre>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "2877241", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-04T17:17:14.490", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2015-04-04T16:59:39.110", "ParentId": "29448997", "CommentCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "2877241", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-04T17:17:14.490"}, "29448997": {"ViewCount": "1878", "Body": "<p>I want to declare length of array with global variable. But I got error, I am confused for solving this. </p>\n<pre><code>int BARIS = 8;\n//I get error when declare Squares Array with global variable (BARIS variable)\nint SquaresInfo[BARIS];\n\nint main(int argc, const char * argv[]) {\n    cout &lt;&lt; \"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t Tekan ENTER untuk masuk ke permainan\";\n    if(cin.get() == '\\n' ) {\n        system(\"clear\");\n        cout &lt;&lt; \"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\";\n        gameInterface();\n    } else {\n        cout &lt;&lt; \" \";\n    }\n\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><img alt=\"enter image description here\" src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/WQqu5.png\"/></p>\n<p>I get error when declare length of SquareInfo array. I am confusing how to declare array length with global variable </p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "29449097", "Title": "How to declare length of global array with global variable?", "CreationDate": "2015-04-04T16:51:13.227", "Id": "29448997", "CommentCount": "5", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-04T17:23:43.717", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "4407626", "Tags": "<c++><arrays>", "AnswerCount": "4"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_29448997_29449097_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.5833333333333334, "section_id": 407}}, "n3337": {"so_29448997_29449097_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.5833333333333334, "section_id": 6895}}, "n4659": {"so_29448997_29449097_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.5833333333333334, "section_id": 425}}}, "29449254": {"Id": "29449254", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Besides the other answers may point out solutions for the c-style array definition (you need a <code>constexpr</code> that can be used to specify the array size at compile time), I'd like to encourage using <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/array\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>std::array&lt;&gt;</code></a> as proposed by the current standard instead:</p>\n<pre><code>std::array&lt;int,8&gt; SquaresInfo;\n</code></pre>\n<p>The current size can be obtained using the <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/array/size\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>SquaresInfo::size()</code></a> function elsewhere.</p>\n<p>Accessing certain indices will be bounds checked, and also it provides much more type like behavior (e.g. automatic copying along assignment operations), than a c-style array does.</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "1413395", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-04T17:23:43.717", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2015-04-04T17:16:27.133", "ParentId": "29448997", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "1413395", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-04T17:23:43.717"}, "29449078": {"Id": "29449078", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>You can't have a variable array index, try</p>\n<pre><code>#define BARIS 8\nint squareInfo[BARIS];\n</code></pre>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-04T16:57:28.173", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2015-04-04T16:57:28.173", "ParentId": "29448997", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "880760"}, "29449062": {"Id": "29449062", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Just move the array definition inside your main function and/or declare BARIS const </p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-04T16:56:09.123", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2015-04-04T16:56:09.123", "ParentId": "29448997", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "4402325"}});